inn1.comm: starts off with a loosener down the leg side, clips his thigh en route to the keeper who dives to his left
punched uppishly, gets on the front foot and just beats the right of mid-off, Zimbabwe are underway
pitches outside off and shapes away from the right hander, left alone
that was a jaffa, kicks off a good length outside off and that has the batsman hopping, mighty close to that edge
pitches on middle and leg, tucked with soft hands to the on side
the straighter one, lands on middle and continues with the line, he offers the full face of the bat and defends
pitches outside off and moves away just a touch, more of a warm-up delivery to start with
hits a good length on off stump and the ball goes through dead straight, gets a good stride forward and defends
walks down the pitch before the ball is delivered, tries to force it past midwicket but gets the placement wrong
pushes it just wide of mid-off to pick up a single
drives with force and tries to beat cover, Butt does brilliantly in that position to intercept it with one hand
not quite short enough to pull, the ball lobs off his pads and nearly rolls onto his stumps, that was rather close to shaving the leg stump
tucked away just wide of mid-on, they runs through quickly and the non striker beats the throw
full and swinging in on leg stump, tries to work if off his wrists but the ball clips the pads, Tanvir appeals half heartedly
gets this to swing in from outside the off stump, pushed back to the bowler
gets forward a little too early and the ball catches him flush on the thigh
short of a length on middle, Sibanda reads the length early, swivels and pulls with intent over square leg, one bounce and four, that stroke was a picture of confidence
pitches just wide outside off, Sibanda cuts hard and backward point just gets a hand to it, they scamper through for a couple
hits a good length outside off, the ball holds its line as it leaves the batsman
pitches outside off again, he shoulders arms
adjusts his line to middle and leg, he tucks it with his wrists and beats square leg
this one is a little shorter, climbs on him, he gets up high and defends
fuller in length, he gets down and defends with soft hands in front of point and sets off
excellent running, he taps it down with soft hands to the off side and some good coordination between the pair results in an easy single
pitches just a shade outside off and moves away just a tad, he shoulders arms
pitches just outside leg, tries to turn it to fine leg, fails to make contact
tries to whip it through the on side again, he's early on the stroke and the ball makes contact with his pads again
tapped with sift hands just in front of mid-off, Masakadza calls early and they set off

superb delivery..... pitches on middle and shapes away, Sibanda is forced to play at it, he pokes at the ball rather uneasily and gets a thick outside edge to Akmal. He doesn't wait for umpire Ghauri to give him out and just walks
pitches outside the off stump, left alone
full outside off, in the slot to drive, punches it hard on the front foot and just manages to beat the left of mid-off
fullish in length outside off, he gets forward and defends to extra cover
has him slashing outside the off stump, poor ball and equally poor shot
holds the length back outside off, adjusts his line closer to the off stump, he gets on the back foot and tries to force it through the off side, just beats the outside edge
better shot, covers the line and forces it back to the bowler
pitches outside the off stump  and straightens, he takes the safe option and shoulders arms
pitches outside the off stump, left alone
loses his line, strays wide outside the off stump and the ball moves away, wide called

Tanvir strikes again! pitches outside the off stump, gets a bit more bounce this time, Chibhabha gets a half prod forward, doesn't know whether to play at it or not, gets a thick outside and the ball flies to Misbah at first slip
pitches outside off and shapes away, Taibu watchfully lets it go
pitches fuller outside the off stump, goes for the drive and is beaten
Appeal: gets forward, the ball strikes him high on the pad around the off stump, Tanvir belts out an appeal, perhaps the ball struck him outside the line of off stump
fuller on leg stump, driven through the line just wide of mid-on
pushed with soft hands in front of cover, they set off immediately and scamper through for the single
short of a length outside off, the ball comes on a little slowly, allows him time to transfer his weight on the back foot and punch it wide of extra cover
pitches outside off, goes through with the line, left alone to the keeper
run-out opportunity, Butt gathers the ball at gully, Masakadza starts off, then gets sent back and the throw was wide of the stumps and the batsman was a mile away
cramps him for room outside the off stump, he plays close to his body and gets an inside edge to the on side
defended to the off side
bangs it in outside off, gets more pace this time, the ball kicks as it leaves the batsman
fuller in length on off stump and swinging away after pitching, Taibu does well to leave that alone
strays wide outside the off stump, left alone
gets the ball to drift in to the right hander this time and makes him play, pushed back to the bowler
strays down the leg side, Taibu tries to work it fine and misses
gets a big stride forward and pushes it towards point, Butt does well to slide to his right and cuts it off

full and wide outside off, Taibu stretches forward, tries to scoop it over the off side but opens the face of the bat at the point of contact. As a result, the ball lobs over the slips and goes down to third man
pitches on off and middle, defended back to the bowler
hits a good length outside the off stump, left alone
pitches just outside the off stump, he covers the line and defends back to the bowler
stays on the back foot and pushes to the off side
done in by the bounce a little, he stays back but ends up meeting the ball low on the front pad just outside the off stump, he pushes it to the on side
overpitches just outside the off stump, he leans forward, meets the line of the ball and forces it to the left of mid-off
pitches on middle and leg, Masakadza gets in position early, shuffles a little and works it with his bottom hand and forces it just wide of midwicket
fuller delivery outside off, goes for the drive and is beaten
adjusts his line to middle and leg, shuffles and works it wide of square leg
pushes it softly in front of cover, Masakadza yells and sends Taibu back
pitches outside off and comes in a tad after pitching, Masakadza plants his foot forward for the drive but changes his mind and chooses to let it go
pitches outside off and moves away, Masakadza is tempted on the stroke again and just manages to withdraw the bat
pitches outside off and moves away, left alone again
lands on off stump and comes in a little, it's a good line as it cramps him for room
overthrows.... pushed with soft hands in front of mid-on, Yousuf under arms the ball at the non striker's end but there was no-one to back that throw
he errs in by sliding down the leg side, he uses his wrists and flicks through the line and just beats the fine leg fielder
fullish on the pads, driven to mid-on
full and swinging in just a touch, he gets forward and pushes it firmly to mid-on
full and angling in towards the pads, Masakadza gets his wrists working again and flicks uppishly just wide of square leg, he manages to bisect the gap between midwicket and square leg
hits a good length on middle, defended back to the bowler
just a touch too wide outside off, he opens the face of the bat and glides it just wide of point
drifts towards the pads,he tucks it just wide of midwicket
hits a good length outside off and gets the ball to straighten, he has the batsman poking at it outside the off stump
edged and....just wide of second slip. Taibu wafts at it outside off and gets a thic outside edge
gets the ball into the right hander this time and the batsman covers the line and defends
defended back to the bowler
gets this straighten after pitching outside off, defended to the off side
flighted on off and middle, defended back to the bowler
gets across his stumps, defended close to the pads, the ball catches the edge and lobs off the pads
attemps a reverse sweep but it doesn't come off well, tamely pushes it to the off side
attempts another reverse sweep, this time he opts out of the stroke and leaves it
the change of ends doesn't work for Rao as he strays full and wide outside off, Masakadza waits on it, scoops it over the gap between backward point and cover and makes full use of that freebie
Strays on the pads, Masakadza gets a half stride forward, lofts through the line of the ball and flicks over midwicket
pitches outside off, glided with an open face to the off side
Third powerplay taken
the slog sweep, Taibu doesn't get the distance but it lucky enough as the ball lands just short of deep backward square leg who runs to his right
digs it in short, he reads the length early, swivels and pulls over square leg, Tanvir is rather lazy getting to it and tries to stop it with his foot
bangs it in short outside off again, he goes for another pull but isn't in full control of the stroke, the ball flies off the top edge over the slips
pushed past the infield on the off side and Masakadza brings up his fifty
worked just wide of midwicket for a single
flighted on middle, he gets down on his knee early and sweeps, a sloppy effort by Salman Butt at square leg results in a free boundary down to long leg..poor stuff there
pitches on middle, the ball stops on him as he chips it towards mid-on who's a little too deep
pushed in front of cover and they set off, Afridi was a little lazy getting to it
fullish on the pads, defended softly to mid-on
flighted outside off, defended back to the bowler
bowls it slightly short and wide outside off, rocks back and cuts
flighted outside off, defended close to the pads
gets forward, defends close to the pads back to the bowler
slides down the leg side, tries to nudge it down to fine leg but the ball meets the pads instead of wood, beats the keeper
shortish and slightly wide outside off, cut to sweeper cover
full outside off and driven to the covers
tossed up outside off, cut to the off side
just a touch too wide outside off, tranfers his weight on the back foot and cuts to sweeper cover
defended back to the bowler
slower ball, lands on a good length, he goes back and cuts to sweeper cover
glided in front of point with very soft hands, excellent coordination between the two results in a quick single
excellent running again, this time he taps it in front of mid-off and sets off
he walks across his stumps to distract the bowler, pitches outside off, he gets a thick outside edge past point, not a very convincing stroke in the end
pushed to the offside, Taibu yells and refuses the run
pushed firmly to the direction of the bowler, Khan runs across and intercepts the ball, Taibu sets off and changes his mind wisely
beaten.... that's a rarity, pitches outside off and beats him for a bit of pace
slides down leg, worked to fine leg
slow half tracker outside off, he has all the time in the world to rock back and cut to the fielder in the deep on the off side
defensive push just wide of point
opens the face of the bat and works it towards point
glided just of point for a single
cut just wide of cover for a single
walks across his stumps, he's toying with the bowler here, he tucks it away with little full behind square on the on side and helps himself to a couple
walks across his stumps again, this time he defends back to the bowler
banged in short, this time he pulls but isn't in full control of it, the fielder at deep midwicket runs forward and nearly takes it on the full, the ball lands on the first bounce
defended on the front foot
short and a touch too wide the off stump, Taibu rocks back and cuts firmly to deep cover
pushed softly to mid-off
tossed up down the leg side, worked to the on side
bowls it a little too short outside off again, he cuts to sweeper cover and they bring up the 100-run stand
wide outside off, cut to sweeper cover again
defended back to the bowler
slashed hard and brilliantly stopped at cover
Khan isn't exerting himself much, he waits on it and pushes to long-on
they're milking the singles here, shuffles across his stumps and works it wide of midwicket
short of a length and a touch wide outside off, Taibu cuts and Tanvir at sweeper cover is too lazy to bend down and gather the ball and instead stops it with his foot
short on middle and leg, Taibu swivels and executes a short arm pull just wide of midwicket for a boundary
grants him width outside off again, the fielder at the deep on the on side intercepts the cut
short and wide, cut hard towards the covers, good reflexes by the fielder
tossed up on lmiddle and leg, pushed to long-on
fullish and side outside off, punched to Jamshed at sweeper cover
flighted on middle, pushed to long-on
gives it more air, pushed to long-on
tossed up slowly outside off, he waits on it, opens the face of the bat and glides it just in front of short third man, good running again
pushed towards midwicket
gets forward to defend, the ball lobs off the pads towards the region of forward short-leg
defended back to the bowler
pitches outside off, cut to the off side
pushed in front of the region of mid-off
defended close to the pads, Afridi appeals and there may have been bat on it
driven back to the bowler
slides down leg, the ball deflects off Akmal's gloves and rolls to short fine-leg
flighted outside off, lands on a fullish length, driven to the off side
glided towards short third man
gets a bit of turn, defended back to the bowler
flighted outside off, defended back to the bowler
defended to the on side, he needs the single for his fifty
flighted outside off and defended again
nudges it behind square on the on side and he still can't get the single
flighted down the leg side, he gets the single and brings up a well-deserved half-century
cut to sweeper cover
gets forward and defends to cover
gets on the back foot and punches it wide of long-on
superb running...slides down the leg side, he works it to deep midwicket and catches the fielder napping by calling for the second run
pitches outside off, cut to sweeper cover
slides down the leg side, wide called
pitches on a good length outside off, cut just wide of point
glided with soft hands in front of short third man and brilliant running again
tossed on middle and leg, turned to midwicket
flighted on leg, turned to square leg
turned to midwicket
flighted on middle and leg, pushed through the line to long-on
tossed up outside off, pushed towards point
full and driven back to the bowler
Masakadza misses his ton.... pushed in flat and quicker outside off,Masakadza shapes to cut close to his body but the ball doesn't turn, he gets a thick inside edge onto middle stump
driven to the off side
tries to drive through the off side but gets an inside edge
gets another inside edge and the ball trickles to the on side
starts off with a half tracker, he pulls with intent and pulls with intent and just beats the diving midwicket
beaten.....that was a jaffa! pitches on off, turns away just a touch and just beats the edge and off stump, Younis is beaming and why not!
short and pulled to the on side
driven back and well fielded
defended back to the bowler
full and driven back to the bowler
driven firmly and some brilliant commitment by Younis at cover cuts off a few runs
inside edge onto the pads
played behind square leg for a single
cut to extra cover, quick single taken
defended towards mid-off
pushed in flat and fast on the pads, Taylor's a little late getting his bat down on it
cramps him for room, defended back to the bowler
Younis errs by giving him too much width outside off, Taylor rocks back, opens the face and cuts hard to beat short third-man
chipped uppishly in the region of mid-off
druven through the line towards long-on
tossed up outside off, driven back to the bowler
cut towards point
tossed on middle and leg, worked just wide of midwicket
full and wide outside off, driven to sweeper cover
turned towards square leg for a single
holds the length back outside off, punched back to the bowler
slides down leg, Taylor gives room and drives to long-on
full outside off and driven down to long-on
full outside off and driven to long-off
b>Dropped: tossed up outside off, he leans onto the stroke a little too early, chips it on the up, Younis gets a hand to it over his head and spills the catch
the first of the match..... flighted on middle and leg, Taylor gives room, steps down the track and lofts over the bowler's head
gives it plenty of air, Taibu feasts on a low full toss and spanks it past extra cover for a boundary, poor bowling there by Younis
pushed towards midwicket for a single
flighted outside the off stump, glided to short third man
flighted down leg, midwicket slides to his left and cuts it off
flighted outside off, he scoops it to long-off
pushed to the off side
short of a length on off and middle, Taibu rocks back, pulls over midwicket but can't fetch a boundary
much fuller, Taibu gets down and slog sweeps over square leg
bowls from round the wicket, gets the ball to drift into off stump, pushed towards the covers, Taylor isn't interested in a run
the slower ball, effective this time as taibu slashes hard outside the off stump and misses
slides down the leg side, Tanvir loses his line
slides towards the pads again, tries to flick it fine but the ball catches him high on the body and rolls to the keeper
slides down the leg side again, Tanvir struggles to control the movement
fullish on middle and leg, pushed through the line to long-on
flighted outside off, closes the face of the bat and turns it in front of square leg
pitches outside off and cuts in a little, goes back and cuts to point
glides in front of short third man, Afridi is too lazy to come forward and stop it, allowing an easy single
defended back to the bowler
pitches outside off, he goes back and cuts to backward point
full and swinging in, driven through the line with force to long-off
the slower one, lands outside off, he waits on it and cuts to short third man

the slower ball again, pitches on a fullish length outside off, Taylor tries to loft over the off side but stays rooted to the crease, Malik runs backwards from extra cover and takes a well-judged catch
slides towards the pads, Tainu helps it on its way and flicks uppishly towards fine leg
tries to work up some swing from outside off, Chigumbura leans forward and defends to the off side
hits a good length outside off, he stays back and cuts to the off side
goes for the wild slog but misses it completely outside the off stump

Pakistan are pulling it back here.... gives it plenty of air outside the off stump, Chigumbura stays at the crease and tries to go downtown, he connects but fails to get the desired elevation, Younis runs to his left from deep midwicket and takes it low forward
Dropped: lofted down to long-off, Rao pedals backwards and tries to take it one-handed and spills it, he ought to have got both hands behind the ball though
swept to fine leg
flighted on off, defended on the front foot
bowls over the wicket to the left hander, pitches outside off, Williams can't beat the off side field
backs away from the stumps, Williams is deceived by the slower ball and ends up chipping it tamely just wide of cover
full outside off, in the slot to drive, Taibu can't beat cover
Tanvir sees Williams charging down the track and switches to a yorker length outside off, Williams tries to dig it out but misses
the slower ball again, he steps down and nearly scoops it to mid-off

Akmal gets the thin edge.... slower ball outside the off stump, Taibu gives room and tries to cut, the ball kicks up a little, gets a thin edge through to Akmal. Taibu knows it and he starts walking before umpire de Silva raises the finger
the bowling change works..... deceives Williams with a slower one, he lofts from the crease and tries to clear long-on, he fails to get the distance and hits it down substitute Fawad Alam's throat
bowls the yorker outside off, digs it out and gets a single to the on side off the inside edge
fullish and angling into the right hander, tucked through the line to the on side
pushed towards point

Rao gets him with reverse swing... gets the ball to drift in from off and middle, Matsikenyeri tries to work it through the off side, gets beaten and the ball cannons onto the leg stump, sending it back a few yards
full outside off and defended on the front foot
bowls from round the wicket.....full and angling in, worked through the line to long-on
gets the ball to drift into the right hander again, he closes the face of the bat and tucks it to the on side
gets it to dip in close to the pads, Khan appeals for a leg before but he may have got an inside edge, the ball rolls towards third man
full outside off and driven to long-off
sliding down the leg side, he follows the line of the ball and pushes it softly to the on side
full and swinging in outside off, pushed through the line to long-off
slower ball outside off, he waits on it and chops it down to the off side
pushed back to the bowler, the ball deflects off his palm to the off side, allowing a single
full and in the slot to loft, Utseya lifts it over the region of mid-on and the ball falls short of long-on
driven on the full towards extra cover
aims for a inswinging yorker, Utseya takes it on the full and chops it onto his boot, he's in a bit of pain
full toss, swinging in to Brent, he follows the line of the ball, sweeps past short fine leg and picks his spot well
switches to over the wicket, he bangs it in short of a length, Brent gives it the treatment by pulling over midwicket. That's consecutive boundaries
hits a good length outside off, he goes for the shot too early and misses
slower ball, Brent goes for a mighty heave and misses again
swing and a miss, Brent stays rooted to the crease and doesn't watch the ball, the ball almost grazes the top of middle stump
on the blockhole on off stump, Brent digs it out to long-off for a single

inn2.comm: starts off with a full one outside off, Butt pushes through the line  just wide of mid-off
holds the length back, pitches on leg, tries to work it through the on side, gets caught on the pads
hits a good length on middle and leg, Jamshed shuffles and tucks it wide of square leg
hits a good length outside off, defended back to the bowler
grants him a bit width outside off, he stays back at the crease and chops it to cover
similar delivery, pitches outside off and shapes away, pushed to cover again
a touch too wide outside off stump and Jamshed drives in the air, safely, over a leaping point fielder ... was hit uppishly but the shot was always on
again there's width and he runs it towards gully, where its well stopped
full outside off stump, he drives with an inside-edge to midwicket, that attempted drive hit with too much bottom hand
just too wide from Brent, and Butt drives into the gap at cover for two
thats a better length, but wide enough for Butt to leave it be
still he struggles to locate his length, and Butt twirls the wide delivery into that gap in the covers, for a single this time
sees a wide one and drives hard, clubbing into the ground in front of point
chases a wide one with a loose walking drive, getting a thick outside-edge wide of the slips and Brent, diving around at third man, cannot save four
quicker one, angled away from Butt at a good height and he leaves
chases another wide one, slamming it past point out to the sweeper
goes fishing for a sharp delivery angling wide of off stump, his feet not moving as he plays away from his body and gets beaten
touch short and he drives off the back foot, to backward point
good length, Butt walks into it with a nice-looking drive to cover
good length again, he walks into it and inside-edges to point
dropped! he drives one from outside off stump very hard and low to Brent, who fails to snap it up in his follow-through
slower one, he hits through the line and lofts over mid-off for four
shorter one, middle and leg, he shuffles and taps it to leg
gets across quickly and dabs a wide one towards backward point
good ball, that one sitting up sharply off a length as it angles across Butt, who's surprised by the bounce and survives with a thick edge wide of gully
pushed just wide of cover
dug in short of a length on middle and leg, the ball comes on a little slower, Jamshed pulls to long leg
short of a length but Jamshed isn't in full control of the pull, chops it down to mid-on
just a bit of width outside off, he chops it down wide of point for a single
pushed towards the covers
teases him with width outside off, he leans onto it but chops it down to the ground
the slower ball, outside the off stump, Butt meets the ball of the toe edge of the bat and the ball rolls through to the keeper
good length outside off, pushed to point
hits a good length outside off and straightens, Butt covers the line and punches it firmly but can;t beat mid-off
pitches on middle and leg, pushed back to the bowler
gets back and defends back to the bowler
not short enough to pull, Jamshed has an ugly swipe at it and misses, Taibu spills the catch though we're not sure if there was an edge. the bowler falls over after delivery
better, waits for the ball, turns the wrists and tucks it wide of midwicket
pitches around the off stump, he gets back and defends to the off side
gets forward, meets the line of the ball and pushes it confidently to cover
hits round about a good length outside off, another defensive push to cover

loose stroke, pitches on a good length on middle and shapes away, the ball bounces a bit more than expected and Butt lunges forward instead of staying back, he flashes at it and gets a thick edge through to Taibu
good stroke, Brent gives him plenty of width outside off, Jamshed stays at the crease and square drives past backward point
takes the aerial route this time, half volley outside off, Jamshed stays at the crease, waits on it and lofts through the line over wide mid-off
good length outside off, pushed towards the covers
brings the length closer to the off stump, Jamshed fishes at it and gets beaten, loose shot
pitches outside off, he punches to point
the slower delivery, Jamshed plays it safe and defends on the front foot
hits a good line and length outside off, Younis gets forward and opts to leave it
full outside off and in the slot to drive, Younis pushes forward and Williams does well at cover to intercept it
pitches on middle and leg, gets a half stride forward and pushes to mid-on
pitches it short of a length on off stump and Jamshed makes him pay, he picks the length early, swings across the line and connects well as the ball sails over midwicket
full and wide outside off, he shapes to carve it over extra cover but gets a thick top edge which sails over the slip cordon and down to third man
three for the over.... pitches on the pads, he turns his wrists and flicks it wide of square leg, the fielder chases but the racy outfield just carries the ball through to the rope in a hurty
slides towards the pads, he waits on it and flicks it down to fine leg
short of a length outside off and wide, he gets forward first and then rocks back a little, cuts hard onto the turf and the ball lobs over backward point, third man does the chasing
the slower ball,Younis reads it well and defends forward
pitches on a good length on off stump, defended
the slower ball, good variation, he stays back and defends
he errs in line by giving too much width outside off, he takes the pace off the ball as well and that allows Jamshed the luxury of time to rock back and pick the gap between cover and point
full outside off, gets a big stride forward and pushes to short mid-off
wide outside off, Younis shapes to bludgeon it past the off side but ends up thudding it onto the turf and point has to leap to save it
half volley outside off, Younis drives on the up and just beats the reach of short cover, the fielder at cover dives in vain at the cover boundary
comes forward to defend, gets an inside edge onto his pads
slower ball, defended on the front foot
short of a length on off stump, Younis pulls but doesn't time it well enough as midwicket chases and pulls it back
pitches on off and middle, he turns his wrists and works it to midwicket
fuller in length outside off, covers the line and defends towards mid-off
tries to slice it through the off side, gets an inside edge onto his pads
the slower ball outside off, Jamshed smashes it hard along the turf, plays away from his body and a misfield by Williams at mid-off results in a boundary
driven to extra cover
full outside off, gets forward and drives to cover
full and angling into the right hander, plays across the line and gets an inside edge onto his pads, the ball rolls to the on side
defended back to the bowler
slides just a touch towards the pads, he waits on it and tucks it wide of square leg
good running.... gets forward and pushes it just in front of mid-on with soft hands, he sets off and the fielder hits the stumps at the striker's end
fullish outside off, driven back to the bowler
full and wide outside off, the away movement takes it further
beaten.... kicks off a good length and catches Jamshed by surprise, he sticks his bat out and the ball just beats the edge
shuffles and works it to midwicket
walks across his stumps to distract the bowler, pitches just outside off, he adjusts his stroke and works it towards mid-on
good length outside off, pushed towards point
punched back to the bowler, he leans forward to intercept the ball, it deflects off his palm and rolls to the stumps at the striker's end
fullish in length outside off, pushed to mid-off
gives him width outside off, waits on the ball and glides it delicately to third man
and that's another fifty for Jamshed! Pitches on leg stump, Jamshed is well aware of the field placemnents on the on side as he flicks it wide of short fine leg, the fielder gives up the chase
defended on the back foot to the covers
gives him width outside off, gets a touch forward, gets his bat down nicely and slices it just wide of point and cover to fetch another boundary
switches to round the wicket, hits a good length on off stump, gets back and defends

take that... fractionally short of a length, drifts into the body, Jamshed picks the length early, swivels on the back foot and pulls behind square on the on side. The fielder in the deep had no chance
pitches outside the off stump, defended with soft hands to the off side
the slower ball, slides on the pads, he turns his wrists and works it behind square on the on side with soft hands
good running, very similar to what we saw from the Zimbabweans earlier, Younis taps it down softly in front of cover and sets off quickly
rocks back and punches firmly past the bowler and down to long-on
drops down to cover and sets off for another quick single
pitches outside off, Jamshed pushes it towards deep extra cover
half volley on off and middle, he stays at the crease, lofts through the line and clears mid-off, he was in full control over that
lands on middle and leg, pushed back to the bowler
pitches outside off, he stays back and pushes it back to the bowler
pitches outside off, pushes through the line to long-on
slightly short, tries to pull but ends up chopping it back to Price
driven to mid-on the back foot
tossed up on middle and leg, turned to deep square leg
full and swinging in, Younis reads it well, covers the line and defends
pitches just outside the off stump, Younis waits at the crease, improvises and glides it to third man
wide outside off, the slower delivery, Jamshed stretches out and swings across the line and connects well enough to beat midwicket
full and wide outside off, he gets forward and caresses it past extra cover
superb timing.... short of a length on middle stump, he rocks back and pulls it straight, the ball sails over midwicket and lands just short of the boundary
worked to the on side, a misfield by Price at midwicket costs an extra run
tosses it up slowly, Jamshed gets forward and pushes it wide of long-on
strays wide down the leg side, Younis gets down to sweep but doesn't connect
waits for the ball to turn away, he flicks his wrists and tucks it in front of square leg
flighted on middle, he works it through the line to long-on
pitches outside leg and turns, he flicks his wrists and works it to Brent at deep square-leg
stays at the crease and chips it towards the region of mid-on, cries of 'catch it' but there were no red shirts in sight
attempted reverse sweep, the ball strikes him on the pad outside the line of leg stump and rolls to the on side, Price appeals
tries to slice it past backward point but ends up chopping it down off the toe edge of the bat

Dropped: half volley on middle, Jamshed lofts through the line and the ball appears to be headed over the rope, Brent does well to run across but tries to catch it one-handed, the ball falls just in front of the rope
cut away to backward point
good length on middle, driven to long-on
good length on middle, pushed to mid-on
pitches on middle, worked to midwicket
gets this one to cut back in, cramps him for room to cut, he chops it down to the off side

excellent work by Price....Jamshed punches the ball on the back foot to the left Price, he sets off for a single which wasn't there, Price gathers the ball and in the same action flings it back at the stumps, Jamshed is about a couple of yards short of his crease and he dives in vain
tucked away behind square leg for a single
gets it to loop in on a flatter trajectory, he works it through the line to fine leg

that's two for the over! Yousuf turns it towards Sibanda at midwicket with soft hands and sets off, Sibanda gathers the ball in a flash and flicks it low to the striker's end, a direct hit finds Younis short of the crease. He doesn't wait for the umpire, he just walks off
defended to the off side, and that ends an good over for Zimbabwe. Pakistan are still ahead though
fullish on middle and leg, gets forward and pushes to mid-off
forced through the off side, a good stop at point limits that to just a single and a scampered one that too
driven forcefully through the off side and short cover gets a finger to it, that cuts off the pace of the ball
pushed back to the bowler
full outside off and driven through the line to long-off
similar delivery, pitches on a fullish length outside off and pushes it to long-off
flighted on middle and off, defended back to the bowler
flighted on middle, same result, defended back to the bowler
pushed in flatter and faster, turned to midwicket
cuts back on the pace, rocks back and punches it in front of mid-on
flighted outside off, pushed to short cover
Yousuf turns his wrists and tucks it wide of Sibanda at midwicket again and this time they go through for the run comfortably
pitches outside off, Yousuf offers the full face of the bat and pushes it firmly past the covers
pitches this in line with the stumps and he drives this back to the bowler
slower delivery, driven to mid-off
keeps a little low, defends back to the bowler
pushes this faster, the ball doesn't bounce much, he pushes it back to the bowler
pitches just a tad outside the off stump, pushed to mid-off for a single
flighted outside off, defended, Malik's in no hurry here to capitalise on the Powerplay
flighted on middle, pushed to mid-on
flighted on off and middle, defended back to the bowler

superb stuff from Taibu! Malik lunges forward to drive but the ball catches the toe of his bat, hits his pad and rolls close to the stumps. Taibu gathers the ball and breaks the stumps with Malik short of the crease. Zimbabwe know they've got him and the third umpire reconfirms that
flighted on middle, turned to the on side
flighted on leg, tucked behind square on the on side
pitches outside off, pushed to the off side
defended on the front foot back to Brent
gets back and pushes to extra cover
gets back and drives again to extra cover
the slower ball, slips in the legcutter, he opens the face of the bat and glides it towards short third man
low full toss, he forces it through the line to long-off
flighted on off and middle, defended back to the bowler
flighted outside off, defended on the front foot
gets this one to loop in from outside the off stump, gets a good stride forward and defends
pitches on a good length on middle, he shuffles and tucks it behind square on the on side
looped in on middle stump, gets down on his knee early and sweeps
pushed in fron of mid-on, they go through for a sharp single
pitches on off stump, defended to the on side
pitches on off stump, defended back to the bowler
fullish in length outside off, defended to the covers
pitches on middle, pushed softly to mid-on
driven firmly back down the pitch and Brent does brilliantly to fling himself to his right and save a couple of runs
good length outside off, pushed to the covers
flighted on middle and leg, tucked behind square on the on side
flighted on middle, defended back to the bowler
flighted outside off, gets a good stride forward and defends
flighted outside off, he can't beat cover
flighted on middle and leg, tucked to midwicket
tossed on middle, tucked to square leg
swing and a miss, Yousuf sees a gift outside off and meets with thin air
makes contact with the bat this time as he pushes it to cover
the slower ball, the legcutter, Yousuf pushes it towards mid-off
slides towards the pads, Yousuf turns his wrists and beats square leg to pick up a valuable couple
uses his wrists again and beats the fielder at square leg for another couple, Brent losing his line here
pitches on middle, worked to midwicket
driven towards mid-on
driven to mid-on on the back foot
shuffles across his stumps and works to square leg
tucks it to square leg, Yousuf is a little lazy getting back to his crease not grounding his bat, Taibu whips the bails off and appeals, the third umpire has a look
flighted down the leg side, Yousuf gets down and sweeps to fine leg
flighted on middle and leg, he gets forward, turns his wrists and works it behind square on the on side
pitches outside the off stump, pushed back to the bowler
pitches on middle and leg, turned to the on side
crisp timing....full on middle and off, Misbah gets forward and punches uppishly off the meat of the bat to the right of mid-off, that breaks the shackles for Pakistan
close.... plays close to the body and gets an inside edge onto the pads
pitches outside off, pushed just wide of mid-off
driven towards mid-on
flighted outside off, defended back to the bowler
waits for it to pitch, he rocks on the back foot and punches to the on side
worked behind square on the on side for a single
flighted outside off, defended back to the bowler
gets it to loop in from outside off, Yousuf leans forward and defends
worked just wide of mid-on and the pair take the opportunity for a quick single
that was wide outside off and going further away, Taibu fumbles and the ball rolls behind him
wide outside off again but this time Misbah gets some wood on it and slices to sweeper cover
outside off and cut to sweeper cover again
pitches outside off, tries to cut but chops it down onto the ground
driven to long-off
half tracker outside off and asking to be hit, Misbah waits on it, swivels and pulls high over midwicket and the ball bounces once to the boundary
flighted outside off, pushed to the off side
gets a big stride forward and defends back to the bowler
flighted on middle and leg, defended  back to the bowler
flighted on middle again, gets a big stride forward and defends
flighted on middle stump, Yousuf is intent on seeing him off
same ball, same result, need we say more?
pitches on the off stump line, defended on the front foot
fullish on middle and leg, pushed firmly towards mid-on who does well to dive to his left and cut it off
defended on the front foot
defended on the front foot towards point
pitches on middle and leg line, turns his wrists and works it towards midwicket
tucked away to the on side
the bowling doesn't work as Williams bowls this one wide outside off, he transfers his weight on the back foot and crashes it past extra cover
flighted outside the leg stump, he gets down and sweeps to fine leg
flighted outside off, pushed to the off side
a big overstep, pushed back to the bowler, we have a free hit here
Free Hit: Yousuf gives room, the ball pitches on a good length, Yousuf flat-bats it down to long-on and Price takes the catch, just a single off that ball
tries to work it to the on side but gets a leading edge to the opposite direction
turned towards square leg
pitches outside the off stump, works it through the line to the off side
pitches outside off, cut to backward point
pitches outside the off stump, opens the face of the bat and glides it to short third man

Misbah tries to launch this out of the ground but mis-hits it, he stays at the crease, gets on his knee and the ball is skied for a long time, Taylor at mid-on takes a few paces backwards and takes the catch, falling over to his right
pitches outside the off stump, cuts to sweeper cover
Afridi cuts hard to sweeper cover
pitches outside off, drives through the line to long-off
pitches outside leg, swept to short fine-leg
well played, pitches outside leg, he gets down and sweeps wide of short fine leg
pitches outside leg again, Yousuf sweeps again but he taps it onto the ground behind the keeper
pushed back to the bowler
in the air.....Afridi lofts over mid-off and long-on runs across to his left, there was a hush as the ball was skied, Afrirdi's safe
that's the big one.... half volley on middle and leg, Afridi stays at the crease and picks it off the meat of the bat and deposits it over deep midwicket
pitches outside off, gets forward and drives to extra cover
tries to cut but misses
fired on the blockhole, dug out to the bowler
lands on a fullish length on leg stump, pushed through the line to long-on
flighted outside off, defended
appeal...strikes him on the pad outside the line of leg stump, Taibu appeals
moves across the stumps to distract the bowler, settles for a flick to the on side
shuffles again, though this time he beats the infield on the on side
flighted outside leg, worked behind square
goes for the lofted off drive outside off, misses it completely
Dropped: Yousuf drives on the up forcefully on the front foot, Chibhabha at mid-off throws himself to his right and nearly pulls off a stunner with both hands
turned to the on side for a couple
Afridi goes for the lofted drive but Brent's there in the deep at long-off to cut it off
pitches outside off and cut to third man
driven towards long-on
gives himself room outside off, he rocks back and bludgeons this through the gap between cover and extra cover
uses his feet, steps down the track and lofts this one over extra cover, two bounces and four
gives room outside leg, Afridi checks his stroke and works this to long-on
swept away behind square on the on side
pitches on a fuller length outside off, Afridi drives to long-off and keeps the strike
wide outside off, thats a gift for Afridi as he gives room and lofts over the infield on the off side, he places it to the left of long-on, the fielder dives but the ball was too quick for him
on the blockhole, dug out to the on side
pushed behind point for a single

Dropped: Masakadza the culprit.... Afridi goes for broke and mis-hits it, the ball is skied for an eternity and the bowler tries to get under it but loses sight as the ball slips through his fingers, the crowd aren't complaining
cut away wide of point and the sweeper cover runs across to cut it off
driven on the front foot to extra cover
pitches outside off, Afridi opens the face of the bat and glides it down to third man
pitches outside off, gets on the back foot and punches to the covers
good length on off stump, gets it to drift in, Yousuf shows the full face of the bat and defends
fuller in length outside the off stump, Yousuf digs it out to the Dabengwa at mid-off
pushed to the off side, good over by Chigumbura so far
Chigumbura keeps him quiet again, Yousuf defends back to the bowler and gives Afridi the strike
Dropped: but a brilliant effort by Sibanda, Afridi slices uppishly on the front foot, Sibanda runs to his left, nearly catches it one-handed, he appears to have it in control but the ball slips out
cut away off the meat of the bat to deep extra cover
full toss on middle and leg, Afridi pulls but can't beat midwicket
good length on middle and leg, Afridi stays back and pulls with intent over midwicket, there was nobody there to cut it off
on the blockhole outside the off stump, he digs it out to mid-off
half volley outside off, Afridi stays at the crease, gets his bat down and scoops through the line and deposits the ball over long-off
defended quietly on the front foot
slides towards the pads, Yousuf responds to the calls of the crowd by taking a single, he nudges to the on side

down the leg side, Afridi decides to let it go and waits for the umpire's call. He can't seal it with a six. The crowd won't mind though because they've witnessed yet another victory at this ground. That's seven out of seven
